HEADWORD: Lithobilic
<hw>Lith`o*bil"ic</hw> <pr>(-b⟦icr⟧l"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Litho</ets> + <ets>bile</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to or designating an organic acid of the tartaric acid
series, distinct from lithofellic acid, but, like it, obtained from
certain bile products, as bezoar stones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

